Author:  PAUL
Vol / Page:  60
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Hake Merluccius australis</i> ... Also occurs off South America. Sometimes called English hake, from a similarity to a north-east Atlantic species; ... Quite different from the unrelated gemfish, but sometimes confused by the erroneous use of `hake' for gemfish in some localities. called English hake by fishermen.
